cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about Bayesian neural networks and their probabilistic inference using variational Bayes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses an application of heteroscedastic regression, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper introduces a novel empirical Bayes procedure, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
